Additional Terms for Pottery Data
While the software code is provided under the MIT License above, please note:
Form Preset Data
The pottery form presets included in this application (clay weights, glaze amounts, etc.) are provided as educational examples based on real pottery practice. These measurements may vary significantly based on:

Individual throwing techniques
Clay body characteristics
Kiln and firing variations
Regional pottery traditions

Use these presets as starting points only. Always verify measurements and costs against your own pottery practice.
Disclaimer for Business Use
This software is designed to assist with pottery cost calculations, but:

You are responsible for verifying all calculations
Pottery costs vary widely by region, supplier, and technique
The authors provide no warranty for business decisions made using this tool
Always consult with experienced potters and business advisors for commercial applications

Attribution (Optional but Appreciated)
While not required by the MIT License, if you find this tool helpful, we'd appreciate:

A mention of Creek Road Pottery in your pottery studio or website
Sharing improvements back to the community via GitHub
Recommending the tool to other potters who might benefit

Contact for Pottery-Specific Questions
For questions about pottery techniques, costing practices, or regional variations:

GitHub Issues: Technical problems with the software
Pottery Communities: Business and technique questions
Local Pottery Guilds: Regional pricing and practice guidance

The MIT License ensures this tool remains free and accessible to the pottery community while allowing potters to adapt it to their specific needs.

This license reflects the values of gratitude, generosity, and empathy that guide this project.
